nstagram.com&amp;_nc_gid=DTyI_A1uVImn02FsMX5KQw&amp;_nc_ss=7a338&amp;oh=00_AfwfSo5vLQ31Tfi-09hM-Fk-1VGZow9dkKMnS7y0ATFvtg&amp;oe=69CA4769" alt="Slide 3 fra @sorenpeter" style="max-width: 48%; margin: 0 1% 8px 0;" /><img src="https://scontent-cph2-1.cdninstagram.com/v/t51.75761-15/484987251_18299765272212227_6638073705581143970_n.jpg?stp=dst-jpg_e35_tt6&amp;_nc_cat=107&amp;ig_cache_key=MzU5MTgxMzk1MTExODM0NTgzNA%3D%3D.3-ccb7-5&amp;ccb=7-5&amp;_nc_sid=58cdad&amp;efg=eyJ2ZW5jb2RlX3RhZyI6InhwaWRzLjEwODB4MTM1MC5zZHIuQzMifQ%3D%3D&amp;_nc_ohc=iARDx_sTt_0Q7kNvwHpU2At&amp;_nc_oc=Adp9FKH-qZjj296c0NV0-D5CLLFqSrAQ0OTyoiTB04HhgcOoP0s9V-Yb2KhcOibrmV8&amp;_nc_ad=z-m&amp;_nc_cid=0&amp;_nc_zt=23&amp;se=7&amp;_nc_ht=scontent-cph2-1.cdninstagram.com&amp;_nc_gid=DTyI_A1uVImn02FsMX5KQw&amp;_nc_ss=7a3ba&amp;oh=00_Afxf_c4xpW2oWW24YXT6qfBjJi9sl4f3j3AeYqQZkAjddQ&amp;oe=69CA401A" alt="Slide 4 fra @sorenpeter" style="max-width: 48%; margin: 0 1% 8px 0;" /></p><p><strong>🖼️ Slideshow (12 medier)</strong></p><p><strong>@sorenpeter</strong></p><p>Artist-in-focus: Søren Peter Langkjær Bojsen<br/>
<br/>
Søren Peter Langkjær Bojsen is a Copenhagen-based film director currently working on ANOTHER WORLD, a documentary series produced in collaboration between Morph and Frau Film. In the series, Søren Peter explores the internet in pursuit of alternatives to the dominant virtual worlds offered by multinational conglomerates. Over the course of six episodes, the project searches for more human and hopeful online spaces and new kinds of meaning within the big, confusing mess that is our age.<br/>
<br/>
Dealing with high-paced sci-fi storytelling, Søren Peter’s previous work similarly investigates fundamental existential challenges of being human in the late modern world. Søren Peter graduated from the alternative film school Super16 in 2018 with his punk sci-fi feature film A Report on the Party and the Guests. He has since won a Robert Award for Best Youth Film for his second feature film, The Great Glitch/Children of Paradise (2023), as well as directed a theatre play titled Monkeys Reacting to Magic (2024) at Aveny-T in Copenhagen.<br/>
<br/>
— <br/>
<br/>
We are thrilled to see that our premiere of Søren Peter’s series ‘Another World’ on Friday is sold out! CPH:DOX has been so kind to give us an additional screening on the 28th of March, 19.00h. Book tickets on their website, link in bio.</p><p><a href="https://www.instagram.com/p/DHYr8TsMGrS/">Se slideshow på Instagram</a></p>]]></description>
